# Obsidian Knowledge Base Rules

## Purpose

The Obsidian vault is the human-readable knowledge layer. It stores:
- Entity cards (drugs, diseases, companies, targets)
- Source cards (PDFs, PubMed, ClinicalTrials, FDA, EMA, patents)
- Run notes
- Reports (scientific, market, patent/finance, final)
- Human decision notes
- Templates

## Vault structure

```text
vault/
  00_inputs/
    {date}_{inn}_{disease}_input.md
  01_entities/
    drugs/{slug}.md
    diseases/{slug}.md
    companies/{slug}.md
    targets/{slug}.md
  02_sources/
    pdfs/{pdf_id}.md
    pubmed/PMID_{pmid}.md
    clinicaltrials/NCT_{nct_id}.md
    fda/FDA_{application_number}.md
    ema/EMA_{medicine_slug}.md
    patents/US{patent_number}.md
  03_runs/
    {run_id}.md
  04_reports/
    scientific/{run_id}_scientific_memo.md
    market/{run_id}_market_memo.md
    patent_finance/{run_id}_patent_finance_memo.md
    final/{inn}_{disease}_report.md
  05_decisions/
    {run_id}_human_verification.md
  99_templates/
    drug_template.md
    disease_template.md
    patent_template.md
    run_template.md
```

## Drug entity card

Must include YAML frontmatter with:
type, preferred_name, inn_ru, inn_en, synonyms, atc, molecule_type, last_updated, source_runs

Sections: Identity, Mechanism, Approved indications, Known brands, Safety, Patent notes, Linked diseases

## Disease entity card

Must include: type, preferred_name, synonyms, subtypes, mesh, icd, last_updated, source_runs

## Run note

Must include: type, run_id, inn, disease, status, input_hash, pdf_hashes, created_at
Sections: Input, Status, Intake enrichment, Scientific output, Market output, Patent/finance output, Final synthesis

## Report notes

Every report must include YAML frontmatter: type, run_id, inn, disease, status, created_at, source_count, model, prompt_version

## Linking

Use Obsidian links: drug -> disease, memo -> sources, run -> memos, sources -> runs

## Citation style in memos

```text
[source: PMID_123456]
[source: NCT_01234567]
[source: FDA_NDA_123456]
[source: EMA_PRODUCT_SLUG]
[source: PDF_source_1_p12_c03]
```

## Writing rules

- Do not duplicate full raw API payloads in Obsidian
- Preserve manual edits below AUTO-GENERATED markers
- Use stable filenames based on slugified names
